'''Dattatraya Bhikaji Kulkarni''' is a [[Marathi people|Marathi]] writer, critic, retired university professor and freelance writer belonging to [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. He was born on 25 July 1934, in [[Nagpur]].<ref name="DuttAkademi1999">{{cite book|author1=Kartik Chandra Dutt|author2=Sahitya Akademi|title=Who's who of Indian Writers, 1999: A-M|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QA1V7sICaIwC&pg=PA637|accessdate=16 May 2012|year=1999|publisher=Sahitya Akademi|isbn=978-81-260-0873-5|pages=637}}</ref> He has been head of department of Marathi at the [[Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj Nagpur University]], of which he is also the alumni.<ref name="RTMNU">{{cite web|url=http://rtmnu.digitaluniversity.ac/Content.aspx?ID=666|title=Department Of Marathi|publisher=Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj Nagpur University|accessdate=16 May 2012|location=Nagpur|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120526194435/http://rtmnu.digitaluniversity.ac/Content.aspx?ID=666|archivedate=26 May 2012|df=}}</ref> He was the president of the 83rd [[Akhil Bharatiya Marathi Sahitya Sammelan]], held in March 2010 in [[Pune]].<ref name="IE-20100117">{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/d-b-kulkarni-sahitya-sammelan-president/568241/|title=D B Kulkarni Sahitya Sammelan president|date=2010-01-17|work=indianexpress.com|publisher=The Indian Express Limited|accessdate=16 May 2012|location=New Delhi}}</ref>
